    {
      "id": "msg_07637789c765520d0169cc4682b31c8195bada61f0894f4169",
      "type": "message",
      "status": "completed",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "output_text",
          "annotations": [],
          "logprobs": [],
          "text": "Summary of require_approval for the Responses API MCP tool\n\nWhat it controls\n- Whether the Responses API pauses to ask for your approval before executing a tool call to a remote MCP server or connector.\n- When approval is required, the API inserts an mcp_approval_request item; you must reply with an mcp_approval_response (approve: true/false) to continue.\n\nDefault\n- By default, approval is required before any data is sent to a remote MCP server/connector.\n\nWhere to set it\n- In each MCP tool entry you pass to responses.create (or session.update for Realtime). It\u2019s a property on the MCP tool shape alongside type, server_url/connector_id, allowed_tools, etc.\n\nValid values and behavior\n- \"always\": Always require approval for tool calls (explicit form of the default).\n- \"never\": Never require approval for any tools from that MCP server (no approval prompts).\n- Per-tool skip: An object that whitelists specific tool names to bypass approval:\n  - require_approval: { \"never\": { \"tool_names\": [\"tool_a\", \"tool_b\"] } }\n  - Those tools won\u2019t prompt for approval; all others still will.\n\nFlow notes\n- If approval is required, you\u2019ll receive an mcp_approval_request in the response output. Approve or reject by sending an mcp_approval_response (you can chain via previous_response_id).\n\nDocs used\n- MCP and Connectors \u2013 Approvals: https://developers.openai.com/api/docs/guides/tools-connectors-mcp/#approvals\n- Realtime API with MCP \u2013 Configure an MCP tool (shows tool shape with require_approval): https://developers.openai.com/api/docs/guides/realtime-mcp/#configure-an-mcp-tool\n- Realtime API with MCP \u2013 Approve or reject MCP tool calls: https://developers.openai.com/api/docs/guides/realtime-mcp/#approve-or-reject-mcp-tool-calls"
        }
      ],
      "role": "assistant"
    }
  ],
  "parallel_tool_calls": true,
